    <h1 style="text-align: center;">Master of Computer Applications (MCA)</h1>

    <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            The Master of Computer Applications (MCA) is a two-year or three-year postgraduate degree program in computer science and applications. It focuses on advanced programming techniques, system management, and IT applications to prepare students for professional roles in software development and IT management.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Course Highlights</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Duration: 2 years (4 semesters) for lateral entry, 3 years (6 semesters) for regular entry</li>
            <li>Eligibility: Bachelor's degree (preferably BCA, B.Sc. in Computer Science, or equivalent) with mathematics at the 10+2 level or at graduation</li>
            <li>Focus Areas: Advanced programming, software engineering, AI, and IT management</li>
            <li>Career Opportunities: Software Architect, Data Scientist, IT Consultant, Project Manager</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Core Subjects</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Advanced Programming (Java, Python, .NET)</li>
            <li>Data Structures and Algorithms</li>
            <li>Database Management Systems</li>
            <li>Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence</li>
            <li>Cloud Computing</li>
            <li>Mobile Application Development</li>
            <li>Cybersecurity</li>
            <li>Software Project Management</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Skills Developed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Expertise in software development and programming</li>
            <li>Proficiency in modern IT tools and technologies</li>
            <li>Project management and leadership skills</li>
            <li>Understanding of machine learning and AI algorithms</li>
            <li>Problem-solving and critical thinking</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Career Prospects</h2>
        <p>
            MCA graduates are in high demand in the IT industry and related sectors. Common career paths include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Software Developer</li>
            <li>System Analyst</li>
            <li>Data Scientist</li>
            <li>Cloud Architect</li>
            <li>IT Consultant</li>
            <li>Database Administrator</li>
            <li>Project Manager</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Graduates can also explore research opportunities or pursue certifications in specialized fields like AI, data science, or DevOps.
        </p>
    </section>

